@arkn98 instead of using datetime_from_utc_to_local can't we just change

```
from:  str(datetime_from_utc_to_local(event.datetime))
to:      str(event.datetime.astimezone())
```

Python 3.3+ allows omitting the TZ in astimezone() to convert to local.  That was changed in https://peps.python.org/pep-0495/#conversion-from-naive-to-aware

I have upgraded python-driver to [3.28.0](https://github.com/datastax/python-driver/releases/tag/3.28.0).
When running `cassandra-cqlsh-tests.sh` locally I can see the number of failures is the same on `trunk` and on my branch.

@adelapena I think it would be useful to rerun the CI for this patch.

Pushed up an alternate approach to fixing the client mode issues here: https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/fecac728ec945e9b376a5fb2c4af54f337d744cf

Tried to minimize the changes to existing code and the need for making up mock values by bypassing certain paths earlier. Also took some inspiration from what `StressCQLSSTableWriter` does in this case.

@smiklosovic Let me know what you think...
